        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued October 27 at 6:25PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 624 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Simla, or 24 miles southwest of Limon, moving southeast at 50 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Ramah.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
